"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943991","Home Office","false","2018-07-27","<p>Border Force does not release port-specific staffing numbers for national security reasons.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","165474","2018-07-27T13:46:40.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943991/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943991/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943991/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-18","UK Border Force: London Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many UK Border Force officers were (a) recruited, (b) dismissed and (c) retired at (i) Heathrow, (ii) Gatwick, (iii) Stansted and (iv) Luton airports in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","David Hanson","165475"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943992","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-27","<p>It is already a requirement for every dog in the UK to be identified by a microchip and its details to be recorded on a recognised database. This includes dogs imported from outside the UK. We do not consider it is necessary to introduce an additional database along the lines proposed.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-27T12:31:32.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943992/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943992/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943992/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-18","Pets: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of the introduction of a database to log pets' (a) microchip numbers, (b) owners details and (c) date of entry into the UK.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","165547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943993","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-27","<p>Defra has an extensive programme of work focused on preparing for a range of scenarios to make sure we are ready for the point when the UK leaves the EU. This includes ensuring there is a system which will enable the tracking of all movements of animals transported from EU member states to the UK and from the UK to EU member states. The precise nature of our future relationship with the EU is still to be determined and is the subject of negotiation.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-27T12:06:25.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943993/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943993/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943993/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-18","Animals: Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if will develop a tracking system to trace all the movements of animals transported (a) from EU member states to the UK and (b) from the UK to EU member states after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","165548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943994","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-27","<p>Defra will continue to share disease outbreak information with the World Organisation for Animal Health (OIE). This information is publicly available to all countries.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-27T12:19:58.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943994/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943994/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943994/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-18","Disease Control: EU Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether it is his Department's policy to continue to share information with European countries in the event of a disease outbreak after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","165549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943995","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-27","<p>The Government is very keen to see the spirit of our relationship with the EU, including that of the Tripartite Agreement, continue beyond our Exit. We want equines to continue to be able to travel to and from the EU with the minimum of disruption, whilst maintaining high biosecurity and welfare standards. The Government is negotiating our departure from the EU with this in mind and Defra is working with the Department for Exiting the European Union to consider appropriate future arrangements, including those for the movement of equines, under a number of possible scenarios. We are also putting in place contingency arrangements in the event of a no-deal outcome.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-27T13:35:31.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943995/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943995/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943995/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-18","Horses: Transport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether the free movement provision on equines under the Tripartite Agreement with France and Ireland is planned to continue after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","165550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943996","Home Office","false","2018-07-23","<p>Applications for visit visas are considered against Appendix V of the Immigration Rules and on a case by case basis. Detailed information on how UK Visas and Immigration makes decisions on visitor cases is published at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/visit-guidance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/visit-guidance</a>.</p><p>Information on total entry clearance visas (the majority of which are visitor visas) broken down by nationality and outcome (grants, refusals, withdrawals, lapsed) is published in the quarterly Immigration Statistics, Visas data tables volume 1, table vi_02_q, latest edition at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-year-ending-march-2018" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-year-ending-march-2018</a>.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-23T15:50:17.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943996/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943996/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943996/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-18","Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many visitor visa applications were received by UK Visas and Immigration in each of the last five years by country; and what proportion of those applications were refused by country.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","165627"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943997","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-27","<p>There is a general existing requirement under the Welfare of Animals (Transport) (England) Order (2006) that protects all animals during transport. This regulation makes it an offence to cause or be likely to cause injury or unnecessary suffering during transport.</p><p> </p><p>Whilst we remain a member of the EU, we continue to be signed up to the requirements of the Pet Travel Scheme. After we leave we want pet owners to continue to be able to travel to and from the EU with the minimum of disruption whilst maintaining high biosecurity and welfare standards. The Government is negotiating our departure from the EU and Defra is looking at future arrangements, including those for pet travel. We are also putting in place contingency arrangements in the event of a no-deal outcome.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-27T12:07:26.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943997/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943997/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943997/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-18","Pet Travel Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will introduce specific requirements to ensure the welfare of dogs and cats transported to the UK under the Pets Transport Scheme after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","165551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943998","Department for International Trade","false","2018-07-25","<p>The ban on cat and dog fur as introduced by EU Regulation No 1523/2007 will be rolled over as part of the Withdrawal Bill.</p><p>The Government has no plans to remove this ban once we leave the EU.</p>","Meon Valley","George Hollingbery",,"2018-07-25T07:31:01.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943998/answer","Biography information for Sir George Hollingbery","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943998/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943998/answer",,,,,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-07-18","Furs: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether it is his policy that the importation ban on cat and dog fur will be retained after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","165552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943999","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-25","<p>The Care Quality Commission’s recent report on radiology services in England recommends that National Health Service trust boards should ensure that they have effective oversight of any backlog of radiology reports; risks to patients are fully assessed and managed; and staffing and other resources are used effectively to ensure examinations are reported in an appropriate timeframe.</p><p> </p><p>It also recommends that the National Imaging Optimisation Delivery Board should advise on national standards for report turnaround times, so that trusts can monitor and benchmark their performance, and that the Royal College of Radiologists and the Society and College of Radiographers should make sure that clear frameworks are developed to support trusts in managing turnaround times safely.</p><p> </p><p>NHS Improvement is overseeing the NHS’s response to the report and its recommendations and providing support to providers. Some of the other recommendations fall to the relevant professional societies, and the Department is supporting them, where helpful, to meet those recommendations.</p><p> </p><p>Alongside its partners, NHS Improvement will support the National Imaging Optimisation Delivery Board to advise on national standards for report turnaround times so that trusts can monitor and benchmark performance.</p><p> </p><p>Through its Operational Productivity programme, NHS Improvement will also continue to support trusts to improve their imaging services, ensuring that all patients have access to safe and efficient care.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-07-25T10:49:56.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943999/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943999/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/943999/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-18","Radiology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking to tackle variations in radiology reporting timescales.","false","Biography information for Stephen Morgan","Portsmouth South","Stephen Morgan","165695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944000","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-27","<p>Yes.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-27T12:16:51.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944000/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944000/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944000/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-18","Horses: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether it is his Department's policy to continue to implement and enforce equine identification after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","165553"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944001","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-27","<p>We want to secure trade with the EU that is as frictionless as possible, and the continued effective and safe regulation of veterinary medicines.</p><p> </p><p>A responsible government should prepare for all potential outcomes, including the unlikely scenario in which no mutually satisfactory agreement can be reached; this is the approach the government is taking.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-27T12:14:34.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944001/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944001/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944001/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-18","Veterinary Medicine: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps he is taking to ensure the continuation of the agreements for the approval of veterinary medicinal products from European countries after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","165554"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944002","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-24","<p>The General Dental Council (GDC) is the healthcare regulatory body responsible for the regulation of dentists and dental care practitioners in the United Kingdom and is independent of the Government.</p><p> </p><p>The Professional Standards Authority for Health and Social Care (PSA) annually reviews each professional regulator’s performance against its Standards of Good Regulation and publishes its findings.</p><p> </p><p>The most recent GDC report was published by the PSA in November 2017 and covered the 2016/17 period. It found that the GDC met all but one of the 24 standards of good regulation.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-07-24T15:16:27.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944002/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944002/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944002/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-18","General Dental Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent assessment he has made of the performance of the General Dental Council; and what steps he is taking to hold that body to account.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Williams","Stockton South","Dr Paul Williams","165705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944003","Treasury","false","2018-07-25","<p>The government has recently closed a call for evidence on how the tax system or charges can be used to tackle single-use plastic waste. The government received over 130,000 responses, including many views on the definition of single-use plastics. These responses are currently being reviewed. The government is committed to taking action in this area, and will announce its next steps regarding specific policy proposals in the autumn.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-07-25T13:27:24.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944003/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944003/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944003/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-07-18","Nappies: Waste Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, if his Department will consider in its definition of single-use plastics the effect of disposable nappies on the residual waste stream that goes to landfill.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","165480"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944004","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-23","<p>The information is not collected in the format requested.</p><p> </p><p>The following table shows the number of detentions under Section 135 between 1 April 2016 and 31 March 2017.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td>All</td><td>Male</td><td>Female</td><td>Unknown</td></tr><tr><td>All Ages</td><td>354</td><td>212</td><td>134</td><td>8</td></tr><tr><td>15 and under</td><td>1</td><td>1</td><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>16-17</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>18-34</td><td>83</td><td>72</td><td>11</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>35-49</td><td>117</td><td>70</td><td>47</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>50-64</td><td>88</td><td>46</td><td>42</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>65 and over</td><td>57</td><td>23</td><td>34</td><td>0</td></tr><tr><td>Unknown</td><td>8</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>8</td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Mental Health Services Dataset - NHS Digital</p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p> </p><p>1. Counts of events and people produced from the new data sources in 2016/17 are incomplete and should not be compared to previous years. The Background Data Quality Report provides further information on these issues and is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/publications/statistical/mental-health-act-statistics-annual-figures/mental-health-act-statistics-annual-figures-2016-17-experimental-statistics" target="_blank">https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/publications/statistical/mental-health-act-statistics-annual-figures/mental-health-act-statistics-annual-figures-2016-17-experimental-statistics</a></p><p> </p><p>2. A person may be detained more than once during the period so this is a count of detentions not people.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2018-07-23T16:40:12.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944004/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944004/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944004/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-18","Compulsorily Detained Psychiatric Patients","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 17 July 2018 to Question 163564, how many (a) women and (b) men by age group were detained under only section 135 of the Mental Health Act 1983 in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","165595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944005","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-25","<p>The Government is determined to achieve zero avoidable plastic waste and will set out our policies and proposed actions in our Resources and Waste Strategy published later this year. To inform this, Defra officials have recently met the Nappy Alliance which supports the use of reusable nappies, and I have met with Proctor &amp; Gamble to learn about their disposable nappy recycling technology.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-25T16:15:13.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944005/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944005/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944005/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-18","Nappies: Waste Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will make it his policy to support the use of reusable nappies and their effect on removing plastics from the residual waste stream.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","165481"
