ody></table><p> </p><p><em>Source: Traffic Commissioner Annual Reports</em></p><p> </p><p>These figures relate only to the local bus service registered with a traffic commissioner in Great Britain. They do not include those services registered with Transport for London or those in Northern Ireland.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-07-23T14:11:12.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944006/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944006/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944006/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-07-18","Bus Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many cessations of bus services his Department or Traffic Commissioners have been notified of in each of the last five ears, and where in the UK these these been.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","165527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944007","Cabinet Office","false","2018-07-23","<p>In preparation for this year’s Civil Service Pay Remit Guidance, officials met with trade union representatives on a number of occasions.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally I met with the General Secretaries of the FDA, Prospect and PCS trade unions on 27<sup>th</sup> June.</p><p> </p><p>Departments set pay strategies appropriate to their workforce and the public services they deliver; they consult with trade unions as appropriate on these issues.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-07-23T14:33:57.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944007/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944007/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944007/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-07-18","Civil Servants: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when the Government plans to hold consultation and negotiations with Prospect, the Public and Commercial Services Union and the FDA on the Pay Remit Guidance for civil servants.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","165687"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944008","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-07-23","<p>The Government issued the following statement regarding the Hong Kong Special Autonomous Region Government’s plan to ban the Hong Kong National Party on 17 July:</p><p><em>“We note with concern the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region Government plans to prohibit the continued operation of the Hong Kong National Party. The rights to stand for election, of free speech and of freedom of association are enshrined in the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region and the Hong Kong Bill of Rights. </em></p><p> </p><p><em>The UK does not support Hong Kong independence, but Hong Kong’s high degree of autonomy, and its rights and freedoms, are central to its way of life, and it is important they are fully respected.”</em></p><p> </p><p>We have discussed this issue with the Hong Kong authorities.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-07-23T12:24:46.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944008/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944008/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944008/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-07-18","Hong Kong: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the Hong Kong Special Administration Region Government on their plans to prohibit the continued operation of the Hong Kong National Party.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","165501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944009","Department for Transport","false","2018-07-23","<p>On 21 July 2017 the Government announced that tolls at the Severn Crossings would be abolished by the end of 2018. The Department will announce the next steps in due course.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-07-23T13:56:48.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944009/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944009/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944009/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-07-18","Severn River Crossing: Tolls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, from what date the tolls on the Severn Bridges are planned to be removed.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","165515"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944010","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-23","<p>HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service holds data showing failure-to appear rates of defendants mapped against the number of courts and tribunals that have closed in each year. There was no significant increase in failure to attend warrants being issued as a proportion of hearings following the large closure programme of 2011/12.</p><p> </p><p>HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service acknowledges the impact that court closure may have on staff and when implementing a court closure support is offered to staff members in discussing relocation options with them. More broadly, staff morale is monitored annually through the HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service People Survey.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-07-23T16:27:01.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944010/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944010/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944010/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-07-18","Courts: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department has commissioned research on the effect of court closures on (a) non-attendances of defendants and (a) staff morale.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","165529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944011","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-23","<p>In January 2018, HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service published its <em>Fit for the future: transforming the Court and Tribunal estate </em>consultation, outlining proposals for its future strategy and approach to the court and tribunal estate in the context of the over £1 billion programme of modernisation currently underway across HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service.</p><p> </p><p>Access to justice, of which proximity to courts and tribunals is one factor, was referred to in the consultation, which closed on 29 March 2018. We are currently considering responses to the consultation and will publish our response in due course.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-07-23T16:40:07.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944011/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944011/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944011/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-07-18","Courts: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that geographic accessibility to courts does not become a barrier to access to justice as a result of the courts closure programme.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","165530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944012","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-23","<p><em>The number of magistrates required by magistrates’ courts and the Family Court are assessed annually through an established protocol agreed with the Judiciary. This can be found at </em><a href="https://www.judiciary.uk/publications/protocol-support-jud-deployment-in-mags-cts/" target="_blank">https://www.judiciary.uk/publications/protocol-support-jud-deployment-in-mags-cts/</a>.</p><p> </p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-07-23T16:22:28.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944012/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944012/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944012/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-07-18","Magistrates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps he is taking to ensure magistrates courts are adequately staffed with magistrates.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","165531"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944013","Home Office","false","2018-07-23","<p>Border Force speaks to industry and consumer bodies on a regular basis and discussions often cover performance against Service Level Agreements.</p><p>Border Force performance against Service Level Agreements is kept under review and Border Force is directly accountable to the Home Office Permanent Secretary and the Home Secretary.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-23T16:03:24.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944013/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944013/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944013/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-18","Immigration Controls: Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 3 July 2018 to Question 158773, whether his Department consults aviation and consumer stakeholders in its reviews of the Service Level Agreements (SLAs) on UK Border Force performance.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","165605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944014","Home Office","false","2018-07-23","<p>Border Force delivery against Service Level Agreements, along with other performance indicators, is kept under constant review. Border Force seeks to provide an effective service at the border by achieving the right balance in its contribution to both the security and prosperity of the UK; objectives considered as complimentary and mutually supportive.</p><p>It is our strategic intent to increase the use of e-Passport gates and other related technologies to provide enhanced security outcomes whilst also facilitating the clearance of passengers. The Government is open to working with partners to enhance Border Force capability, whether that is through better targeted interventions, or improved service standards.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-23T15:45:42.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944014/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944014/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944014/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-18","Immigration Controls: Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will make it his policy to ensure that UK Border Force service standards are raised and expected waiting times lowered as a result of airport spending on ePassport gate technology to improve throughflow of passengers at the border.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","165606"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944015","Home Office","false","2018-07-23","<p>Border Force delivery against Service Level Agreements, along with other performance indicators, is kept under constant review. Border Force seeks to provide an effective service at the border by achieving the right balance in its contribution to both the security and prosperity of the UK; objectives considered as complimentary and mutually supportive.</p><p>It is our strategic intent to increase the use of e-Passport gates and other related technologies to provide enhanced security outcomes whilst also facilitating the clearance of passengers. The Government is open to working with partners to enhance Border Force capability, whether that is through better targeted interventions, or improved service standards.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-23T15:48:26.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944015/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944015/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944015/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-18","Immigration Controls: Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether UK Border Force plans to improve its service to non-EEA passengers on their arrival in the UK in order to attract trade and investment from those countries after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","165607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944016","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-07-23","<p>Yes. The National Shipbuilding Strategy (page 33) set out that Offshore Patrol Vessels should be subject to open international competition, provided that there are no compelling national security reasons to constrain a particular procurement to national providers.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-07-23T16:04:05.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944016/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944016/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944016/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-07-18","Patrol Craft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 16 July 2018 to Question 162497 on Patrol Vessels, and with reference to his Department's policy of not classifying offshore patrol vessels as warships for shipbuilding purposes, as outlined in the Answer of 9 July 2018 to Question 160710, whether possible future Royal Navy orders for offshore patrol vessels will be subject to international competition.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","165493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944017","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-07-23","<p>​We have not raised this specific issue with the Israeli authorities. However we remain concerned about Israeli restrictions on freedom of movement and access into and out of the Occupied Palestinian Territories, and we continue to raise these wider concerns with the Israeli authorities.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-07-23T16:48:21.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944017/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944017/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/944017/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-07-18","Occupied Territories: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, recent discussions he has had with his Israeli counterpart on the Israeli Government's policy of restricting access to the Occupied Palestinian Territories for international visitors; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Dan Carden","Liverpool, Walton","Dan Carden","165688"
