d Lidington","165135 ; 165137 ; 165138","2018-07-23T09:04:10.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942951/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942951/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942951/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-07-17","Conflict, Stability and Security Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which countries were allocated funding from the Conflict, Stability and Security Fund in (a) 2017 and (b) 2018; and what the value was of those allocations.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","165136"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942952","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-07-23","<p>The Voluntary Right to Buy Midlands Pilot will be launching later in the summer, and ahead of the launch we will announce details of the housing associations who will be taking part in the pilot, and how eligible tenants will be able to apply for the scheme.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-07-23T14:34:38.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942952/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942952/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942952/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-07-17","Right to Buy Scheme: Birmingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will list the housing associations with properties within (a) Birmingham Northfield constituency and (b) Birmingham who are eligible for the Voluntary Right to Buy Midlands pilot scheme for housing association tenants; and how many tenants he estimates will take part in that scheme in both of those areas.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","164839"
