"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942977","Treasury","false","2018-07-25","<p>The Government is making additional funding available so that departments and the devolved administrations can prepare effectively for EU Exit.</p><p>At Autumn Budget 2017 we made an additional £3 billion available for 2018-19 and 2019-20 (£1.5bn each year) on top of £700 million additional funding previously announced.</p><p>The devolved administrations are receiving their full share of additional funding in devolved areas through the Barnett Formula. Through this process the Northern Ireland Executive departments have so far been allocated an additional £2.35m in 2017-18 and £15.2m in 2018-19.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-07-25T11:17:32.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942977/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942977/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942977/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-07-17","Northern Ireland Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much the Government has spent on preparing Northern Ireland Executive departments for the UK leaving the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Nigel Dodds","164904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942978","Treasury","false","2018-07-23","<p>The LIBOR grant scheme was closed following the announcement of the final tranche of funding at Autumn Budget 2017. All LIBOR fines received from the Financial Conduct Authority have been committed.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-07-23T13:18:43.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942978/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942978/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942978/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-07-17","LIBOR","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much LIBOR funding he has yet to allocate.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","165031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942979","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-23","<p>The Government proposal to increase the small claims track limit, for road traffic accident related personal Injury claims to £5,000 and for all other personal injury claims to £2,000, is intended to reduce the costs associated with this type of civil litigation.</p><p> </p><p>The Government published a validated impact assessment for the measure alongside the Civil Liability Bill on 20 March 2018. It contains analysis, data and assumptions including both the estimated costs and savings to all sectors, including the insurance industry, arising from the increases to the small claims track. The Impact Assessment is available at: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/720954/whiplash-impact-assessment.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/720954/whiplash-impact-assessment.pdf</a>.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-07-23T16:42:21.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942979/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942979/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942979/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-07-17","Small Claims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether he has estimated the cost to the insurance industry of an increase in claims tried using the small claims track as a result of proposed changes to the small claims limit; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","164966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942980","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-07-24","<p>All departments are equipping themselves with the resources they need to get the best deal for the UK. The Department for Exiting the European Union now has over 650 staff based in the UK plus the expertise of over 120 officials in Brussels. We regularly review headcount to ensure we are appropriately staffed to deal with all aspects of the negotiations. <br><br></p><p>The Department is continuing to recruit the brightest and the best and we are not providing a running commentary as recruitment is ongoing and numbers are regularly changing.</p>","Fareham","Suella Braverman",,"2018-07-24T17:06:40.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942980/answer","Biography information for Suella Braverman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942980/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942980/answer",,,,,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-07-17","Department for Exiting the European Union: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many civil servants his Department has employed in each month since July 2016.","false","Biography information for Jenny Chapman","Darlington","Jenny Chapman","164980"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942981","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-23","<p>Details of all Ministerial meetings with external stakeholders are published quarterly in arrears on the GOV.UK website at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministerial-gifts-hospitality-overseas-travel-and-meetings" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministerial-gifts-hospitality-overseas-travel-and-meetings</a></p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","165054 ; 165055 ; 165056 ; 165057 ; 165058 ; 165059 ; 165060 ; 165061","2018-07-23T16:30:24.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942981/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942981/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942981/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-17","Infant Foods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, on which occasions he or Ministers of his Department have met the manufacturers of Aptimil in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","165053"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942982","Attorney General","false","2018-07-23","<p>The National Fund was created in 1928 with the purpose of paying off the entire national debt. At present the fund cannot be used unless it completely clears the national debt, due to the terms of the fund’s charitable trust.</p><p>On 22 May 2018 my predecessor made an application to the High Court to vary the terms of the charitable trust so that the National Fund can be used to help pay down the national debt.</p><p>It is now for the High Court to decide whether the terms of the charitable trust should be varied. If the application is successful the money in the fund will be paid over to the National Debt Commissioners towards the reduction of the national debt.</p><p>I consider that applying the fund in reduction of the national debt is the correct approach. This approach maintains the original charitable purpose of the national fund, namely the reduction of the national debt and it honours the original intention of the donors as a result of whose generosity the fund exists.</p><p>We await a hearing date from the High Court.</p>","Torridge and West Devon","Mr Geoffrey Cox","165033","2018-07-23T09:29:57.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942982/answer","Biography information for Mr Geoffrey Cox","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942982/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942982/answer",,,,,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2018-07-17","National Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, if he will seek the release of money from the National Fund in order to set up a fund for good causes.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","165032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942983","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-23","<p>Details of all Ministerial meetings with external stakeholders are published quarterly in arrears on the GOV.UK website at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministerial-gifts-hospitality-overseas-travel-and-meetings" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministerial-gifts-hospitality-overseas-travel-and-meetings</a></p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","165053 ; 165055 ; 165056 ; 165057 ; 165058 ; 165059 ; 165060 ; 165061","2018-07-23T16:30:24.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942983/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942983/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/942983/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-17","Infant Foods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, on which occasions he or Ministers of his Department have met the manufacturers of SMA infant formula in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","165054"
